# release.env — deployment-local operator policy + secrets (TEMPLATE).
#
# Copy to `release.env` (gitignored, per-machine) to turn on the flags that are
# OFF by code default. BOTH launch paths source it:
#   ./start_proxy.sh   (working-tree proxy)   — sourced; caller env still wins
#   ./run_release.sh   (official :7800)       — sourced
# A fresh clone has NO release.env, so a new laptop runs without these until you
# create one here. This file is just the template — it does nothing itself.
#
# Format: plain KEY=VALUE, one per line; # comments and blank lines ignored.
# Caller-supplied env overrides any line here (e.g. `WS_SPAWNER_HINT=0 ./start_proxy.sh`).

# Spawner discovery hint: inject the self-contained wirescope grammar block into
# spawn-capable MAIN agents (those carrying the Agent/Task tool) so they learn
# the [wirescope:...] directives. Never shown to subagents. Code default: OFF.
WS_SPAWNER_HINT=1

# Operator omit floor: strip these reminder sections from EVERY subagent spawn
# with no per-agent directive (lowest precedence; keep-overridable). Use only
# for unconditional targets — `useremail` is safe; `claudemd` is per-task
# strategy, leave it to the spawner. Comma- or space-separated. Code default: empty.
WS_OMIT_DEFAULT=useremail

# Subscriber callback bearer token (optional) — only if you run push consumers
# that you want gated. See SUBSCRIBERS.md.
# SUBSCRIBERS_TOKEN=change-me
